          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690286224531-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1690286224531-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690286228176-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690286228176-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690286228176-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690286228176-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1690286228176-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>yellow mustard seeds</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind to form a smooth paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and mix well – this is your <strong>mustard mixture</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively blitz together in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690286232093-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690286232093-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690286232093-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690286232093-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690286232093-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>(in its packaging!) in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>(this softens the naturally hard cream)</p><p>Leave for 1 min, then remove from the mug</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and<strong> softened creamed coconut</strong> to the <strong>mustard mixture</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Bengali-style mustard paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1690286235642-x200.jpg",
